- link: https://www.dw.com/en/worldlink-music-to-my-ears/av-51366976?maca=en-podcast_world_link-7211-xml-mrss
  published: Fri, 22 Nov 2019 11:26:00 GMT
  summary: This week on WorldLink, we meet rising pop star Lipa Schmeltzer who's been
    called the Jewish Lady Gaga, and hear the story of how an Uzbek cleaner found
    her passion DJing in night clubs in Moscow. We also speak to the Turkish jazz
    musician credited with creating fusion jazz, and travel to New Zealand, where
    a 2500 year old tree survives in one of the last remaining patches of native forest.
  title: 'WorldLink: Music to my ears'
- link: https://www.dw.com/en/worldlink-striking-a-chord/av-51265903?maca=en-podcast_world_link-7211-xml-mrss
